liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Big news for Spain is that Alexia Putellas starts for Spain. The two-time Balon d'Or winner started against Zambia but has been a sub mostly - and has not managed more than an hour in any game this tournament. She is one of two changes as Olga Carmona comes into the leftback role - and will step up as captain of the side due to Oihane Hernández 's suspension - and Esther González drops out.
